The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Friday, January 16, 2004 				 Calcutta to be CES operational hub 
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Jan. 15: Consulting Engineering Services India (CES), a global infrastructure project management and IT enabled services company currently operating out of Delhi, has decided to shift its operational headquarters to the city.																								With the bandwidth position improving in Calcutta, we could get same productivity at lesser cost, said managing director S. S. Chakraborty.																								The company also plans to set up a business process outsourcing (BPO) facility to cater to overseas clients with 1000 seats at Salt Lake, Chakraborty said. 																								Chakraborty was speaking to reporters after the state information technology minister Manabendra Mukherjee laid the foundation stone for a CES Centre over nearly an acre at Salt Lake. Chakraborty said that the companys manpower requirement in the city could go up to 3000 in BPO and engineering and project management.																								The company is registered with a number of multilateral funding agencies such as the World Bank, Asian Development Bank, African Development Bank, KFW, (Germany), Overseas Economic Co-operation Fund of Japan as a multidisciplinary consultancy organisation. CES is engaged in planning and execution of a host of projects, including environment, energy, infrastructure, information technology, technical training, general construction, traffic and transportation. 																								Apart from India the companys activities are spread over Algeria, Bangladesh, Eritrea, Ethiopia, Georgia, Cameroon, Indonesia, Iran, Kazakstan, Lao PDR, Mauritius, Myanmar, Nepal, Nigeria, Oman, Russia, Sri Lanka, Uganda, United Arab Emirates, United Kingdom and Yemen.																								Chakraborty said the registered and corporate office of CES would remain in New Delhi so that the company can keep in touch with the Union government and multilateral funding agencies. However, the operational headquarters and all additional jobs would come to Calcutta. The hydropower business will be the first to be shifted to the city. The BPO business with domain knowledge engineering and medicine and other customer services would be launched soon. 
